cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on relation extraction from text corpora using neural models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a method for improving the performance of knowledge graph construction, which is a common application of AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses embedding techniques to represent entity pairs and construct an entity proximity graph. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as relation extraction is a common task in information retrieval and the paper proposes a method for improving the performance of this task. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses neural models for relation extraction.
